[
    {
        "name": "City of Davenport",
        "observations": [
            {
                "observation": "Thank you, mayor. So I'm gonna share my thoughts on this matter. First and foremost, I agree with the people that process matters. To give the people a little bit of background, some of it's noted on a green sheet, some of it's not. Executive order was issued November 8 that appointed ICA merit as the interim as of November 17. Obviously, such was done because our administrator left the city of Davenport. Such did not come before the council in 2023. I've heard that there wasn't time for it, but there was time in December of 2023 to ratify three settlements. A new council was seated in January 2024, consisting of five new alderpersons, myself included. Sometime in January, January 23 of 2024, I was asked regarding hire's appointment. I had concerns. I did not sign. I raised those concerns, and thankfully, my concerns were thought out or listened to. And then subsequently, is when we received advice from outside legal accounts that these should be ratified. I do believe that things of this nature should always be done in the public unequivocally. No ands, ifs, or buts should be done in the public, should be done simultaneously. That is how government can be transparent and accountable to its people.",
                "classification": "G",
                "sentiment": "positive"
            },
            {
                "observation": "Now, as I sat up here for multiple meetings where this has come forward, I have listened. I've listened to constituents. I've also listened to my colleagues. I understand my colleagues were elected by the people, whether of the city, entire city of Davenport, or their ward.",
                "classification": "G",
                "sentiment": "positive"
            },
            {
                "observation": "Another constituent said that led the last meeting, that the appointment itself should be separate. I also agree with that. It's something that I've mentioned before, and I do think that today I will be requesting when I'm done speaking, assuming there's no one else that wants to speak for my colleagues, that we motion to separate the two. So that the actual appointment is a vote in and of itself, and then the MOU is a separate vote in and of itself.",
                "classification": "G",
                "sentiment": "positive"
            },
            {
                "observation": "And some of the comments made that I think about and agree with is that process matters, that we have to do better, that the public has lost trust in Davenport. And it's unfortunate. It really is. When I ran for office, I ran because I wanted to make my community better. But little did I know that it would be in breaking in shambles or that it would be like trying to turn the Titanic around. Trying to do my best. I have faith that my colleagues are also trying to do their best with the cards that we have been dealt and trying to move this city forward.",
                "classification": "S",
                "sentiment": "positive"
            },
            {
                "observation": "I do think it's a difficult position that some of us have been placed in because not only did we not have knowledge of everything that took place last year, we're being asked now to make decisions and go retroactively to November of 2023.",
                "classification": "G",
                "sentiment": "positive"
            },
            {
                "observation": "With that said, I would motion that item number two be divided or separated. And whereas it would be two votes, the first would be the resolution ratifying executive order 23 2022. Excuse me, 23 22, appointing Mallory Merritt as the interim city administrator. And then a second would then be a resolution regarding the personal memorandum of understanding between the city of Davenport and Mallory. Merit.",
